{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"ramakrishnaTeachings","displayName":"Sri Ramakrishna","version":"1.0","language":"English","edition":"Wikiquote Verified","primaryCategory":"Philosophy & Spirituality","subcategory":"Vedanta","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"groupingLevels":[],"sortPriority":41,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Sri Ramakrishna","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"devotional","audienceTags":["tradition:hindu","theme:god","theme:devotion","audience:spiritual"],"itemCount":120,"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Ramakrishna_Teachings.json"},"data":[{"id":"ramakrishna-0001","text":"Knowledge leads to unity, but Ignorance to diversity. So long as God seems to be outside and far away, there is ignorance. But when God is realised within, that is true knowledge.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0002","text":"Meditate upon the Knowledge and Bliss Eternal, and you will also have bliss. The Bliss indeed is eternal, only it is covered and obscured by ignorance. The less your attachment is towards the senses, the more will be your love towards God.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0003","text":"Those who wish to attain God and progress in religious devotion, should particularly guard themselves against the snares of lust and wealth. Otherwise they can never attain perfection.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0004","text":"Iron, after it is converted into gold by the touch of philosopher's stone, may be kept under the ground or thrown into a rubbish heap; it will always remain gold and will not return to its former condition. Similar is the state of the man whose soul has touched, even once, the feet of the Almighty Lord. Whether he dwells in the bustle of the world, or in the solitude of the forest, nothing ever contaminates him.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0005","text":"It's enough to have faith in one aspect of God. You have faith in God without form. That is very good. But never get into your head that your faith alone is true and every other is false. Know for certain that God without form is real and that God with form is also real. Then hold fast to whichever faith appeals to you.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0006","text":"In the Kaliyuga, man, being totally dependent on food for life, cannot altogether shake off the idea that he is the body. In this state of mind it is not proper for him to say: \"I am He\". When a man does all sorts of worldly things, he should not say, \"I am Brahman\". Those who cannot give up attachment to worldly things, and who find no means to shake off the feeling of \"I\", should rather cherish the idea, \"I am God's servant; I am His devotee.\"","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0007","text":"God made me pass through the disciplines of various paths. First according to the Puranas, then according to the Tantra. I also followed the disciplines of the Vedas...I practised all sorts of Sadhana .... During my Sadhana period I had all kinds of amazing visions.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0008","text":"Many are the names of God, and infinite the forms that lead us to know Him. In whatsoever name or form you desire to call Him, in that very form and name you will see Him.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0009","text":"It is true that God is even in the tiger, but we must not go and face the animal. So it is true that God dwells even in the most wicked, but it is not meet that we should associate with the wicked.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0010","text":"The manifestation of the Divinity must be understood to be in greater degree in those who are honoured, respected, and obeyed by a large following, than in those who have gained no such influence.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0011","text":"As fishes playing in a pond covered over with reeds and scum cannot be seen from outside, so God plays in the heart of a man invisibly, being screened by Miyd from human view.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0012","text":"At a certain stage of his path of devotion, the devotee finds satisfaction in God with form; at another stage, in God without form,","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:action"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0013","text":"When Bhagavdn 5r! Ramakandra came to this world, seven sages only could recognise Him to be the God, incarnate. So when God descends into this world, few only can recognise His Divine nature.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0014","text":"On the tree of Sat-^it-dnanda there are innumerable :' ;Rlmas, Knshwas, Christ's, &c. ; one or two of them come | 'down into this world now and then, and produce mighty changes and revolutions.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0015","text":"It is one and the same Avatara that, having plunged into the ocean of life, rises up in one place and is known as Krishna, and diving again rises in another place and is known as Christ.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0016","text":"This world is like a stage, where men perform many parts under various disguises. They do not like to take off the mask, unless they have played for some time. Let them play for a while, and then they will leave off the mask of their own accord.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0017","text":"The heart of the devotee is like a dry match; and the slightest mention of the name of the Deity kindles the fire of love in his heart. But the mind of the worldly, soaked in lust and greed, is like the moist match, and can never be heated to enthusiasm, though God may be preached to him innumerable times.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0018","text":"A worldly man may be endowed with intellect as great as that of Ganaka, may take as much pains and trouble as a Yogin, and make as great sacrifices as an ascetic; but all these he makes and does, not for God, but for worldliness, honour, and wealth.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0019","text":"As water does not enter into a stone, so religious advice produces no impression on the heart of a worldly I man.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0020","text":"The snake is very venomous. It bites when any one approaches to catch it. But the person who has learnt the snake-charm can not only catch a snake, but carries about several of them like so many ornaments. Similarly, he who has acquired spiritual knowledge can never be polluted by lust and greed.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0021","text":"Samadhi is the state of bliss which is experienced by a live fish which, being kept out of water for some time, is again put into it.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0022","text":"As one can ascend to the top of a house by means of a ladder or a bamboo or a staircase or a rope, so diverse also are the ways and means to approach God, and every religion in the world shows one of these ways.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0023","text":"If God is Omnipresent, why do we not see Him ? Standing by the bank of a pool thickly overspread with scum and weeds, you will say that there is no water in it. If you desire to see the water, remove the scum from the surface of the pond. With eyes covered with the film of maya you complain that you cannot see God. If you wish to see Him, remove the film of Maya from off your eyes.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0024","text":"Knowledge leads to unity, and Ignorance to diversity.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0025","text":"As persons living in a house infested by venomous snakes are always alert and cautious, so should men living in the world be always on their guard against the allurements of lust and greed.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0026","text":"When the tail of the tadpole drops off, it can live both in water and on land. When the tail of ignorance drops off, man becomes free. He can then live both in God and in the world equally well.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0027","text":"If a man prays to Thee with a yearning heart, he can reach Thee, through Thy grace, by any path.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0028","text":"God is directly perceived by the mind, but not by this ordinary mind. It is the pure mind that perceives God, and at that time this ordinary mind does not function. A mind that has the slightest trace of attachment to the world cannot be called pure. When all the impurities of the mind are removed, you may call that mind Pure Mind or Pure Ātman.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0029","text":"God reveals Himself to a devotee who feels drawn to Him by the combined force of these three attractions: the attraction of worldly possessions for the worldly man, the child's attraction for its mother, and the husband's attraction for the chaste wife. If one feels drawn to Him by the combined force of these three attractions, then through it one can attain Him.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:action","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0030","text":"God can be realized through all paths. All religions are true. The important thing is to reach the roof. You can reach it by stone stairs or by wooden stairs or by bamboo steps or by a rope. You can also climb up by a bamboo pole.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0031","text":"Women are, all of them, the veritable images of Śakti.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0032","text":"With sincerity and earnestness one can realize God through all religions. The Vaishnavas will realize God, and so will the Saktas, the Vedantists and the Brahmos. The Mussalmans and the Christians will realize him too. All will certainly realize God if they are earnest and sincere.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0033","text":"I had to practise each religion for a time — Hinduism, Islām, Christianity. Furthermore, I followed the paths of the Śāktas, Vaishnavas, and Vedāntists. I realized that there is only one God toward whom all are travelling; but the paths are different.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0034","text":"Once someone gave me a book of the Christians. I asked him to read it to me. It talked about nothing but sin. Sin is the only thing one hears at your Brahmo Samaj too... He who says day and night, ‘I am a sinner, I am a sinner’, verily becomes a sinner... Why should one only talk about sin and hell, and such things?","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0035","text":"Whether you accept Rādhā and Krishna, or not, please do accept their attraction for each other. Try to create that same yearning in your heart for God. Yearning is all you need in order to realize Him.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:action"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0036","text":"Can you weep for Him with intense longing of heart? Men shed a jugful of tears for the sake of their children, for their wives, or for money. But who weeps for God? So long as the child remains engrossed with its toys, the mother looks after her cooking and other household duties. But when the child no longer relishes the toys, it throws them aside and yells for its mother. Then the mother takes the rice-pot down from the hearth, runs in haste, and takes the child in her arms.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0037","text":"Lovers of God do not belong to any caste. … A brāhmin without this love is no longer a brāhmin. And a pariah with the love of God is no longer a pariah. Through bhakti an untouchable becomes pure and elevated.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0038","text":"One should not think, \"My religion alone is the right path and other religions are false.\" God can be realized by means of all paths. It is enough to have sincere yearning for God. Infinite are the paths and infinite the opinions.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0039","text":"I have heard that man can acquire superhuman powers through it and perform miracles. I saw a man who had brought a ghost under control. The ghost used to procure various things for his master. What shall I do with superhuman powers? Can one realize God through them? If God is not realized then everything becomes false.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0040","text":"He who has realized God does not look upon a woman with the eye of lust; so he is not afraid of her. He perceives clearly that women are but so many aspects of the Divine Mother. He worships them all as the Mother Herself.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0041","text":"This māyā, that is to say, the ego, is like a cloud. The sun cannot be seen on account of a thin patch of cloud; when that disappears one sees the sun. If by the grace of the guru one's ego vanishes, then one sees God.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0042","text":"One cannot be spiritual as long as one has shame, hatred, or fear.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:courage"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0043","text":"As for me, I consider myself as a speck of the dust of the devotee's feet.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0044","text":"Direct the six passions to God. The impulse of lust should be turned into the desire to have intercourse with Atman. Feel angry at those who stand in your way to God. Feel greedy for Him. If you must have the feeling of I and mine, then associate it with God. Say, for instance, \"My Rama, my Krishna.\" If you must have pride, then feel like Bibhishana, who said, \"I have touched the feet of Rama with my head; I will not bow this head before anyone else.\"","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0045","text":"It is not good for ordinary people to say, \"I am He.\" The waves belong to the water. Does the water belong to the waves? The upshot of the whole thing is that, no matter what path you follow, yoga is impossible unless the mind becomes quiet. The mind of a yogi is under his control; he is not under the control of his mind.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind","theme:yoga"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0046","text":"By constantly repeating, \"I am free, I am free\", a man verily becomes free. On the other hand, by constantly repeating, \"I am bound, I am bound\", he certainly becomes bound to worldliness. The fool who says only, \"I am a sinner, I am a sinner\", verily drowns himself in worldliness. One should rather say: \"I have chanted the name of God. How can I be a sinner? How can I be bound?\"","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0047","text":"The body was born and it will die. But for the soul there is no death. It is like the betel-nut. When the nut is ripe it does not stick to the shell. But when it is green it is difficult to separate it from the shell. After realizing God, one does not identify oneself any more with the body. Then one knows that body and soul are two different things.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:soul","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0048","text":"Who may be called a paramahamsa? He who, like a swan, can take the milk from a mixture of milk and water, leaving aside the water. He who, like an ant, can take the sugar from a mixture of sugar and sand, leaving aside the sand.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0049","text":"The waves belong to the Ganges, not the Ganges to the waves. A man cannot realize God unless he gets rid of all such egotistic ideas as \"I am such an important man\" or \"I am so and so\". Level the mound of \"I\" to the ground by dissolving it with tears of devotion.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0050","text":"One can easily realize God if one is free from guile. Spiritual instruction produces quick results in a guileless heart. Such a heart is like well cultivated land from which all the stones have been removed. No sooner is the seed sown than it germinates. The fruit also appears quickly.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0051","text":"When the fruit appears the blossom drops off. Love of God is the fruit, and rituals are the blossom.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0052","text":"Live in the world like a waterfowl. The water clings to the bird, but the bird shakes it off. Live in the world like a mudfish. The fish lives in the mud, but its skin is always bright and shiny.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0053","text":"If there are errors in other religions, that is none of our business. God, to whom the world belongs, takes care of that.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0054","text":"Imagine a limitless expanse of water: above and below, before and behind, right and left, everywhere there is water. In that water is placed a jar filled with water. There is water inside the jar and water outside, but the jar is still there. The \"I\" is the jar.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0055","text":"I have no disciple. I am the servant of the servant of Rama.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0056","text":"All will surely realize God. All will be liberated. It may be that some get their meal in the morning, some at noon, and some in the evening; but none will go without food. All, without any exception, will certainly know their real Self.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0057","text":"The Pure Mind and the Pure Ātman are one and the same thing. Whatever comes up in the Pure Mind is the voice of God.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0058","text":"If one has faith one has everything.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0059","text":"Many people think they cannot have knowledge or understanding of God without reading books. But hearing is better than reading, and seeing is better than hearing. Hearing about Benares is different from reading about it; but seeing Benares is different from either hearing or reading.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0060","text":"There is not a fellow under the sun who is my disciple. On the contrary, I am everybody's disciple. All are the children of God. All are His servants. I too am a child of God. I too am His servant.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0061","text":"One cannot attain divine knowledge till one gets rid of pride. Water does not stay on the top of a mound; but into low land it flows in torrents from all sides.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0062","text":"You have been born in this world as a human being to worship God; therefore try to acquire love for His Lotus Feet. Why do you trouble yourself to know a hundred other things? What will you gain by discussing philosophy? Look here, one ounce of liquor is enough to intoxicate you. What is the use of your trying to find out how many gallons of liquor there are in the tavern?","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:love","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0063","text":"There are three kinds of devotees: superior, mediocre, and inferior. The inferior devotee says, \"God is out there.\" According to him God is different from His creation. The mediocre devotee says: \"God is the Antaryami, the Inner Guide. God dwells in everyone's heart.\" The mediocre devotee sees God in the heart. But the superior devotee sees that God alone has become everything; He alone has become the twenty-four cosmic principles. He finds that everything, above and below, is filled with God.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0064","text":"You see many stars in the sky at night, but not when the sun rises. Can you therefore say that there are no stars in the heavens during the day? O man, because you cannot find God in the days of your ignorance, say not that there is no God. (Sutra 1)","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0065","text":"He is born in vain, who having attained the human birth, so difficult to get, does not attempt to realise God in this very life.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0066","text":"Little children play with dolls in the outer room just as they like, without any care of fear or restraint; but as soon as their mother comes in, they throw aside their dolls and run to her crying, \"Mamma, mamma.\" You too, are now playing in this material world, infatuated with the dolls of wealth, honour, fame, etc., If however, you once see your Divine Mother, you will not afterwards find pleasure in all these. Throwing them all aside, you will run to Her.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:courage"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0067","text":"Water and a bubble on it are one and the same. The bubble has its birth in the water, floats on it, and is ultimately resolved into it. So also the Jivatman (individual soul) and the Paramatman (supreme soul) are one and the same, the difference between them being only one of degree. For, one is finite and limited while the other is infinite; one is dependent while the other is independent.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0068","text":"As the snake is separate from its slough, even so is the Spirit separate from the body.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0069","text":"Men are like pillow-cases. The colour of one may be red, that of another blue, and that of the third black; but all contain the same cotton within. So it is with man; one is beautiful, another is ugly, a third holy, and a fourth wicked; but the Divine Being dwells in them all.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0070","text":"When an unbaked pot is broken, the potter can use the mud to make a new one; but when a baked one is broken, he cannot do the same any longer. So when a person dies in a state of ignorance, he is born again; but when he becomes well baked in the fire of true knowledge and dies a perfect man, he is not born again.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0071","text":"As the cloud covers the sun, so Maya hides the Deity. When the cloud moves away, the sun is seen again; when Maya is removed, God becomes manifest.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0072","text":"If you can find out the nature of Maya, the universal illusion, it will leave you just as a thief runs away when detected.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0073","text":"Those who wish to attain God or make progress in their devotional practices should particularly guard themselves against the snares of lust and wealth. Otherwise they will never attain perfection.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0074","text":"Try to gain absolute mastery over the sexual instinct. If one succeeds in doing this, a physiological change is produced in the body by the development of a hitherto rudimentary nerve known as Medha (the function of which is to transmute the lower energies into the higher). The knowledge of the higher Self is gained after the development of this Medha nerve.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0075","text":"The mind steeped in affection for ‘woman and gold ’ is like the green betel-nut. So long as the betel-nut is green, its kernel remains adhering to its shell, but when it dries up shell and nut are separated, and the nut moves within if shaken. So when the affection for women and gold dries up, the soul is perieved as quite different from the body.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0076","text":"As 'persons living in a house infested with venomous snakes are always alert, so should men diving in the world be always vigilant against the allurement of lust and greed.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0077","text":"The sun can give heat and light to the whole world, but he cannot do so when the clouds shut out his rays. Similarly as long as egotism veils the heart, God cannot shine upon it.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0078","text":"The vanities of all others may gradually die out, but the vanity of a saint regarding his sainthood is hard indeed to wear away.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0079","text":"If you feel proud, let it be in the thought that you are the servant of God, the son of God. Great men have the nature of a child. They are always a child before Him; so they are free from pride. All their strength is of God and not their own. It belongs to Him and comes from Him.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0080","text":"As a piece of rope, when burnt, retains its form, but cannot serve to bind, so is the ego which is burnt by the fire of supreme Knowledge.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0081","text":"That knowledge which purifies the mind and heart alone is true Knowledge, all else is only a negation of Knowledge.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0082","text":"Common men talk bagfuls of religion but do not practise even a grain of it. The wise man speaks little, even though his whole life is religion expressed in action.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:action"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0083","text":"The nearer you come to God, the less you are disposed to questioning and reasoning. When you actually attain Him, when you behold Him as the reality, then all noise, all disputations, come to an end.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0084","text":"Only two kinds of people can attain to self-knowledge: those who are not encumbered at all with learning, that is to say, whose minds are not over-crowded with thoughts borrowed from others; and those who, after studying all the scriptures and sciences, have come to realize that they know nothing.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind","theme:knowledge","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0085","text":"Do you, O preacher, carry the badge of authority? The humblest servant of the king, authorized by him, is heard with awe and respect, and can quell a riot by showing his badge ; so must you, O preacher, first, obtain your commission and inspiration from God Himself. So long as you do not have this badge of Divine inspiration, you may preach all your life, but it will be mere waste of breath.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0086","text":"When the jar is full, it does not make noise any more. So t}ie man of realization too does not talk much. But what then about Narada and others? Yes; Narada, Sukadeva and a few others like them came down several steps after the attainment of Samadhi, and out of mercy and love they taught mankind.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0087","text":"As a little boy or girl can have no idea of conjugal pleasure, even so a worldly man cannot at all comprehend the ecstasy of Divine communion.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0088","text":"The young bamboo can be easily bent, but the full grown bamboo breaks when it is bent with force. It is easy to bend the young heart towards God, but the untrained heart of the old escapes the hold whenever it is so drawn.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0089","text":"The parrot cannot be taught to sing when the vibrating membrane in its throat has hardened too much due to age. It must be taught to sing while young, before the collar line appears on its neck. So in old age it is difficult to learn how to fix the mind on God, but it can be easily learnt in youth.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0090","text":"A boat may stay in water, but water should not stay in boat. A spiritual aspirant may live in the world, but the world should not live within him.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0091","text":"As a boy holding to a post or a pillar whirls about it with headlong speed without any fear or falling, so perform your worldly duties, fixing your hold firmly upon God, and you will be free from danger.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:courage"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0092","text":"If a white cloth is stained even with a small spot, the stain appears very ugly indeed. So the smallest fault of a holy man becomes painfully prominent.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0093","text":"Forgiveness is the true nature of the ascetic.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0094","text":"Honour both spirit and form, the sentiment within as well as the symbol without.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0095","text":"As a toy fruit or a toy elephant reminds one of the real fruit and the living animal, so do the images that are worshipped remind one of the God who is formless and eternal.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0096","text":"Visit not miracle-mongers and those who exhibit occult powers. These men are stragglers from the path of Truth. Their minds have become entangled in psychic powers, which are like veritable meshes in the way of the pilgrim to Brahman. Beware of these powers, and desire them not.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0097","text":"One does not care for the cage when the bird has flown away from it. and when the bird of life flies away, no one cares for the body left behind.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0098","text":"In a potter's shop there are vessels of different shapes and forms — pots, jars, dishes, plates, etc., — but all are made of the same clay. So God is one, but He is worshipped in different ages and climes under different names and aspects.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0099","text":"Unless one always speaks the truth, one cannot find God Who is the soul of truth.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:soul","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0100","text":"It is very pleasant to scratch an itching ring-worm, but the sensation one gets afterwards is very painful and intolerable. In the same way the pleasures of this world are very attractive in the beginning, but their consequences are terrible to contemplate and hard to endure.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0101","text":"To drink pure water from a shallow pond one should gently take the water from the surface without disturbing the pond in the least. If it is disturbed, the sediments rise up and make the whole water muddy. If you desire to be pure, have firm faith, and slowly go on with your devotional practices, without wasting your energy in useless scriptural discussions and arguments. Your little brain will otherwise be muddled.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0102","text":"The goal can never be reached unless a man makes his mind strong, and firmly resolves that he must realise God in this very birth, nay, this very moment.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0103","text":"Sunlight is one and the same wherever it falls; but only a bright surface like that of water, or of a mirror reflects it fully. So is the light Divine. It falls equally and impartially on all hearts, but the pure and pious hearts of holy men receive and reflect that light well.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0104","text":"Who is whose Guru? God alone is the guide and Guru of the universe.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0105","text":"A thief enters a dark room and feels the various articles therein. He lays his hands upon a table perhaps, and saying \"Not this\" passes on. Next he come upon some other article — a chair, perhaps — and again saying \"Not this\" continues his search, till, leaving article after article, he finally lays his hands on the box containing the treasure. Then he exclaims \"It is here!\" and there his search ends. Such, indeed is the search for Brahman.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0106","text":"Brahman is beyond mind and speech, beyond concentration and meditation, beyond the knower, the known and knowledge, beyond even the conception of the real and unreal. In short, It is beyond all relativity.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind","theme:meditation","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0107","text":"Right discrimination is of two kinds — analytical and synthetical. The first leads one from the phenomena to the Absolute Brahman, while by the second one knows how the Absolute Brahman appears as the universe.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0108","text":"As the shell, the pith and the kernel of the fruit are all produced form one parent seed of the tree, so from the one Lord is produced the whole of creation, animate and inanimate, spiritual and material.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0109","text":"When the head of a goat is severed from its body, the trunk struggles for some time, still showing signs of life. Similarly, though ahamkara (egotism) is slain in the perfect man, yet enough of its vitality is left to make him carry on the functions of physical life; but it is not sufficient to bind him again into the world.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0110","text":"When the tail of the tadpole drops off, it can live both in water and on land. When the tail of delusive ignorance drops off from man, he becomes free. He can then live in God and the world equally well.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0111","text":"With the divine Knowledge of Advaita (non-duality) in you, do whatever you wish; for then no evil can ever come out of you.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0112","text":"Do yourself what you wish others to do.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0113","text":"Men are quick to praise and quick to blame; so pay no heed to what others speak of you.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0114","text":"As long as I live, so long do I learn.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0115","text":"Heaven sometimes speaks through the mouths of lunatics, drunkards and children.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0116","text":"The devil nevetf\" enters the house wherein songs in praise of Hari are always sung.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0117","text":"His name is Intelligence (Chinmaya): His abode is Intelligence; and He, the Lord, is All-Intelligence.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0118","text":"First purify your heart. When the mind becomes pure, the Lord Himself comes and makes it His seat. No image of God can be set up in a dirty place. The eleven bats referred to above are the eleven senses (the five organs of knowledge, the five organs of action and the mind). First dive deep within your own self and get the gems lying hidden there. After that you can have everything else. First you have to enshrine Uddhava in the heart; then you can have enough of lecturing and preaching.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind","theme:knowledge","theme:action","theme:self"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0119","text":"Throughout his life Ramakrishna continued to use words and similes which struck his more sensitive hearers as shockingly crude. But even those who were shocked had to admit that in Ramakrishna's mouth, the words lost much of their offensiveness; for he used them with such innocence.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"ramakrishna-0120","text":"For Ramakrishna, bhakti cannot be defined in a single word, rather, a cluster of words is necessary. … A path will do only if it is characterized by sincerity, earnestness, and single-minded devotion. Only then will we find that all paths lead to God.","author":"Sri Ramakrishna","source":"Ramakrishna","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:god","theme:devotion","theme:wisdom","audience:spiritual","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."}]}